    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Variable term referring to greenish colors resembling the colors of a prasine stone or pigment, or the color of the green stalks of leeks, which are culinary herbs allied to the onion.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046986/Webster's Third New International Dictionary (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指色近於中性磷銅礦礦石或顏料的綠色色彩，或近似於韭蔥綠莖的顏色。韭蔥是烹調用的香草植物，與洋蔥同類。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Variabele term die verwijst naar de groenachtige kleuren die lijken op de kleuren van prasinekleurig steen of pigment, of de kleur van de groene stengels van prei, een keukenkruid dat verwant is aan de ui.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Termo variável que se refere às cores esverdeadas que lembram as cores de uma pedra prasina ou pigmento, ou a cor dos talos verdes do alho-poró, que são ervas culinárias aliadas à cebola.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
